'''Umak Leth''' was an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] engineer. He was one of the chief weapons engineers on the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|original Death Star]].<ref name="DS">[[Death Star (novel)|''Death Star'']]</ref>

==Biography==
During the time leading up to the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], Leth was a representative of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic's]] [[Ministry of Science (Galactic Republic)/Legends|Ministry of Science]]. In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], Leth participated in a [[HoloNet/Legends|HoloNet]] debate opposite [[Nasdra Magrody]] and [[Bunt Dantor]], where he argued that the [[Malevolence/Legends|mysterious weapon]] targeting Republic task forces was possibly equipped with [[Cloaking device/Legends|cloaking devices]]. He estimated that the power supply capable of destroying entire task forces of [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]] would require a vessel to be at least 8 kilometers long. He also speculated that a [[Jenth-class hypermatter core|''Jenth''-class hypermatter core]] was the possible reactor being used for this.<ref name="HNN" />

During the [[Great Jedi Purge/Legends|Great Jedi Purge]], Leth designed the [[Universal Energy Cage]] to hold and transfer [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] captives.<ref name="DESB" /> He also developed the "[[resonator]]" devices, weapons which were used to [[Torture/Legends|torture]]'' and subjugate the [[Marasan]] people.<ref name="GG12">''[[Galaxy Guide 12: Aliens — Enemies and Allies]]''</ref> He also began work on the [[World Devastator]]s as early as 0 BBY, with its development being so secret that Leth only relayed the most basic information to Grand Moff Wilhuff Tarkin, which he then used in the official field manual ''[[Imperial Handbook: A Commander's Guide]]''.<ref name="Imperial Handbook">''[[Star Wars: Imperial Handbook: A Commander's Guide]]''</ref> After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] discredited [[Bevel Lemelisk]], Leth was given the position of [[Master of Imperial Projects]] for his creation of an advanced model of [[molecular furnace]].<ref name="DESB">''[[Dark Empire Sourcebook]]''</ref>

Years later he designed the [[Galaxy Gun]] for the reborn [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]],<ref name="DEII4" /> as well as the [[World Devastator]]s,<ref name="DESB" /> [[SD-10 battle droid]]s, and [[Shadow Droid]]s.<ref name="DEII1">[[Dark Empire II 1|''Dark Empire II'' 1]]</ref> In addition, he presented the cloned Emperor with the [[XR-85 tank droid|XR-85]], allowing the tank droids to finally be fully realized.<ref name="The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia">{{CSWECite|III|344}}</ref> He was killed when Palpatine's flagship ''[[Eclipse II]]'' fell out of hyperspace and collided with the Galaxy Gun.<ref name="NEGC" /><ref name="EE2">[[Empire's End 2|''Empire's End'' 2]]</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
In the [[Empire's End (audio drama)|audio dramatization]] of ''[[Star Wars: Empire's End]]'', Leth was voiced by [[John Cygan]],<ref name="EEAudio">[[Empire's End (audio drama)|''Empire's End'' audio drama]]</ref> and in ''[[HoloNet News — A Galaxy Divided]]'', he was voiced by [[David W. Collins]].<ref name="HNN" />

He was to appear in an additional [[Star Wars comic books|comic]], ''[[Boba Fett vs. The Empire]]'', where Leth would betray the Empire and [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] would be tasked with hunting him down, but the comic was never developed.<ref name="Galaxy">{{CollectorCite|4|ComicScan|ComicScan: Comics That Almost Were}}</ref>

